nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Arginine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: Arginine (C6H14N4O2) is synthesized through a convergent prebiotic network centered on ornithine as the key penultimate intermediate. The guanidinium group of arginine is installed via reaction of ornithine with cyanamide (direct guanidination) or through a urea/citrulline pathway. Ornithine itself derives from glutamate, which is produced either by reductive amination of \u03b1-ketoglutarate (generated via hydrothermal CO2 fixation through a proto-rTCA pathway) or via extended Strecker-type synthesis from HCN and formaldehyde. The network integrates hydrothermal CO2 reduction (formate, formaldehyde, pyruvate), surface photochemistry (cyanamide, urea from HCN), and biochemical assembly (guanidination, condensation). Five hub molecules\u2014HCN, formaldehyde, pyruvate, glutamate, and ornithine\u2014create a densely interconnected network with multiple redundant routes to the target.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CHO2- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C5H6O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C5H9NO4 (glutamic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C5H9NO3 (glutamic gamma-semialdehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C5H12N2O2 (ornithine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: CH4N2O (urea) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C6H13N3O3 (citrulline) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C6H14N4O2 (arginine) [target]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Fischer-Tropsch-type CO2 reduction to formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_006, mol_005 -> mol_007 (Pyruvate synthesis from C1 building blocks) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_007, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_008 (Reductive carboxylation of pyruvate to alpha-ketoglutarate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_008, mol_003 -> mol_009 (Reductive amination of alpha-ketoglutarate to glutamate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005, mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_009 (Extended Strecker synthesis of glutamate from C1 units and HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_009, mol_002 -> mol_010 (Reduction of glutamate to glutamic gamma-semialdehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_008: mol_010, mol_003 -> mol_011 (Transamination of glutamic gamma-semialdehyde to ornithine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_012 (UV photochemical synthesis of cyanamide from HCN and NH3) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_004 -> mol_013 (UV-driven hydrolysis of HCN to urea) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_011, mol_012 -> mol_015 (Direct guanidination of ornithine by cyanamide to arginine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_011, mol_013, mol_003 -> mol_014, mol_015 (Ornithine carbamylation by urea to citrulline and subsequent amination to arginine) [Surface]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal rTCA to glutamate to ornithine, cyanamide guanidination (via formate) (9 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal rTCA to glutamate to ornithine, urea/citrulline pathway (via formate) (9 steps)\n  - P3: Surface Strecker glutamate, hydrothermal ornithine synthesis, cyanamide guanidination (6 steps)\n  - P4: Surface Strecker glutamate, hydrothermal ornithine synthesis, urea/citrulline pathway (6 steps)\n  - P5: Hydrothermal formate-only route to pyruvate, rTCA, reductive amination, cyanamide guanidination (9 steps)\n  - P6: FTT formaldehyde hub pathway with Strecker and cyanamide (6 steps)\n  - P7: HCN-centric pathway: Strecker glutamate + cyanamide from same HCN pool (6 steps)\n  - P8: HCN-centric pathway: Strecker glutamate + urea from HCN (6 steps)\n  - P9: Mixed environment: hydrothermal alpha-ketoglutarate, surface amination, cyanamide (9 steps)\n  - P10: Dual-convergent pathway: hydrothermal + Strecker glutamate, dual guanidination (12 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_005, mol_007, mol_009, mol_011\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\n                \"rxn_001\": 0.90,\n                \"rxn_002\": 0.65,\n                \"rxn_003\": 0.55,\n                \"rxn_004\": 0.55,\n                \"rxn_005\": 0.85,\n                \"rxn_007\": 0.45,\n                \"rxn_008\": 0.70,\n                \"rxn_009\": 0.72,\n                \"rxn_011\": 0.85\n            },\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.64,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.72,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.82,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.80,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.72,